    <text>
        <body>
            <entry xml:id="entry_fawyn" xml:lang="os">
                <form xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>fawyn</orth><form type="participle"
                            ><orth>fawd</orth></form></form>
                <form xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>fawun</orth><form
                        type="participle"><orth>fawd</orth></form></form>
                <sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                        <q>хулить</q>
                    </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                        <q>abuse</q>
                    </abv:tr></sense>
                <abv:exampleGrp>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>næ xærinægtæ... sæ kæræʒījy fawync</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>наши кушанья хулят друг друга</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>our dishes reproach each other</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Коста"/><biblScope>80</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                </abv:exampleGrp>
                <etym xml:lang="ru">Восходит к сильной ступени индоевропейского глагола %iрū-%i ||
                    %ipāv-%i ‘гнить’ || ‘гноить’. Ср. д. %iæm-baw-un%i (←%i*ham-pāv-%i) ‘гноить’,
                    %iæm-buj-un%i (←%i*ham-pū-%i) ‘гнить’. %iFawyn%i, стало быть, означает буквально
                    „делать гнилым“ (хуля, охаивая что-либо). Ср. <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/>
                        <w>pu-, pav-</w>
                        <gloss><q>гнить</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/>
                        <w>pū-</w>
                        <gloss><q>гнить</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="got"><lang/>
                        <w>fūls</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="de"><lang/>
                        <w>faul</w>
                        <gloss><q>гнилой</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="grc"><lang/>
                        <w>πόθω</w>
                        <gloss><q>сгною</q></gloss></mentioned> и пр. См. <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_æmbawun"/>.%n<bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_Miller,_IF_21"/><biblScope xml:lang="ru">стр.
                            333</biblScope><biblScope xml:lang="en">p.
                    333</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
                <etym xml:lang="en">It traces back to a strong ablaut grade of an Indo-European verb
                    %iрū-%i || %ipāv-%i ‘rot’ || ‘make rot’. Cf. Digor %iæm-baw-un%i
                    (←%i*ham-pāv-%i) ‘make rot’, %iæm-buj-un%i (←%i*ham-pū-%i) ‘rot’. Thus,
                    %ifawyn%i literally means ‘make something rotten’ (by abusing, picking on sth.).
                    Cf. <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/>
                        <w>pu-, pav-</w>
                        <gloss><q>rot</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/>
                        <w>pū-</w>
                        <gloss><q>rot</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="got"><lang/>
                        <w>fūls</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="de"><lang/>
                        <w>faul</w>
                        <gloss><q>rotten</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="grc"><lang/>
                        <w>πόθω</w>
                        <gloss><q>I will make it rotten</q></gloss></mentioned> etc. See <ref
                        type="xr" target="#entry_æmbawun"/>.%n<bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_Miller,_IF_21"/><biblScope xml:lang="ru">стр.
                            333</biblScope><biblScope xml:lang="en">p.
                    333</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
            </entry>
